fill up.translation[0].definitions[0].de: if a container or place fills up, or if you fill it up, it becomes full
fill up.translation[0].definitions[0].ex: Her eyes filled up with tears.

fill up.translation[0].definitions[1].de: to eat so much food that you cannot eat any more
fill up.translation[0].definitions[1].ex: Don’t fill yourself up with cookies.
He filled up on pecan pie.
fill up.translation[0].definitions[2].de: food that fills you up makes you feel as though you have eaten a lot when you have only eaten a small amount
fill up.translation[1].definitions[0].de: to gradually become full of people, things, or a substance
fill up.translation[1].definitions[0].ex: Shares on the Stock Market began to rise, and industry reported order books filling up.
